Type: Package
Package: pcurveMix
Title: Computations and Fitting with the P-Curve Mixture Model
Version: 1.0.3
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rolf", "Ulrich", , "ulrich@uni-tuebingen.de", role = "aut"),
    person("Jeff", "Miller", , "miller@psy.otago.ac.nz", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Package for computations and fitting with the p-curve mixture
    model of Ulrich & Miller (2026). According to the model, p values from
    statistical tests come from a mixture distribution with some
    proportion 'pi' of studies having a true effect (H1 is true), whereas
    the remaining studies have no true effect (H0 is true).  Among studies
    with H1 true, the noncentrality parameter is normally distributed with
    mean 'mu' and standard deviation 'sigma'.  Package functions can fit
    the model to a set of observed p values by estimating the underlying
    'pi', 'mu', and 'sigma' values, and they can also provide the model's
    true PDF and CDF values of specific p's given particular values of the
    model's parameters 'pi', 'mu', and 'sigma'.
